docs.summary:
Get the list of transactions for merchant with specified filters.

 Supports pagination.
address details (like street and house number)
Describing physical or business location

Recurring payment is described by `frequency` (day, week, month) and `interval`.

 For example, to create a recurring payment every 14 days, just set `interval` to 14 and frequency to `DAY`.

 In some cases there should be a trial period for the order, after which payments start to occur.
 Trial period is also defined as `frequency` and `interval` pair.

 So one can define a monthly 'subscription' with a 14 days trial period.

members.name: amount
members.doc: Amount which will be refunded. If empty, full refund will be issued.

members.name: reason
members.doc:
Refund reason. Will be passed to provider as is.
 For com.stripe provider you should pass one of predefined reasons, otherwise no reason will be passed to provider.
 Allowed reasons for com.stripe are: "duplicate", "fraudulent", "requested_by_customer".

docs.summary:
Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • DAY
  • WEEK
  • MONTH
  • YEAR

Possible values are:
  • SUBSCRIPTION_UNDEFINED
  • SUBSCRIPTION_ACTIVE - meaning recurring payment is active
  • SUBSCRIPTION_CANCELLED - meaning recurring payment was cancelled by user
  • SUBSCRIPTION_FINISHED - meaning the total billing cycles for the optional trial and the regular payment periods was completed (not yet supported)
  • SUBSCRIPTION_PENDING - meaning recurring payment is not active yet, waiting for the first payment
  • SUBSCRIPTION_SUSPENDED - meaning recurring payment was suspended by user

Possible values are:
  • PARTIAL
  • FULL

Possible values are:
  • PENDING
  • SUCCEEDED
  • FAILED

Possible values are:
  • SALE
  • RECURRING
  • INITIALIZE_RECURRING

Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • INITIALIZED
  • IN_PROCESS
  • APPROVED
  • PENDING
  • PENDING_MERCHANT
  • PENDING_BUYER
  • BUYER_CANCELED
  • TIMEOUT
  • REFUND
  • PARTIAL_REFUND
  • VOID
  • CHARGE_BACK
  • EXPIRED
  • DECLINED
  • FAILED
  • COMPLETED_FUNDS_HELD
  • TPA_CANCELED
  • OFFLINE
  • DISPUTE
  • AUTHORIZED

Possible values are:
  • NA
  • SYNC
  • ASYNC

Possible values are:
  • ALREADY_REFUNDED
  • PROVIDER_IS_DOWN - Provider was killed via feature toggle due to temporal issues
  • NOT_SUPPORTED - Provider doesn't support refunds at the moment, transaction in a wrong state or we don't have required information for this transaction
  • PENDING_REFUND - Refund was started and waiting for confirmation from provider
  • EXPIRED - Transaction is too old
  • FORBIDDEN - Logged in user has no permission to refund this transaction

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • NOT_CLAIMED
  • FUNDS_HELD
  • CLAIMED
  • BLOCKED
  • SUSPENDED
  • MUST_BE_CLAIMED

Possible values are:
  • SELECTED
  • CONNECTED

Possible values are:
  • ONLINE_METHOD
  • OFFLINE_METHOD
